Overcoming Life 's Disappointments ( ISBN 1 - 4000 - 3336 - 5 ) is a 2006 book by Harold Kushner , a Conservative rabbi .
Ally 's World is a series of books written for young adults by Karen McCombie .
Napoléon le Petit ( literally , `` Napoleon the Little '' ) was an influential political pamphlet by Victor Hugo which condemned the reign of Napoleon III , Emperor of the French .
The Godly Man 's Picture is a work of systematic theology by Thomas Watson , a 17th century English Puritan preacher .
`` Wedding Preparations in the Country '' ( German : `` Hochzeitsvorbereitungen auf dem Lande '' ) is an incomplete work by Franz Kafka which depicts in great detail the journey of the groom , Raban , travelling to the country to meet his future wife , Betty .
Sanditon ( 1817 ) is an unfinished novel by the English writer Jane Austen .
The Call of the Toad , published in Germany in 1992 as Unkenrufe , is a novel by Danzig - born German author Günter Grass .
Richard Bolitho , Midshipman is a novel in the Bolitho series , nautical fiction set in the Royal Navy of the late 18th century by Douglas Reeman writing under the pseudonym Alexander Kent .
Life Is Elsewhere ( Czech : Život je jinde ) is a Czech - language novel by Milan Kundera published in 1969 .
Red Seas Under Red Skies is the second novel ( of a projected seven ) in Scott Lynch 's Gentleman Bastard series .
The Timeless Way of Building is a 1979 book by Christopher Alexander that proposes a new theory of architecture ( and design in general ) that relies on the understanding and configuration of design patterns .
Sophie 's World ( Norwegian : Sofies verden ) is a 1991 novel by Norwegian writer Jostein Gaarder .
Der König verneigt sich und tötet ( The King Bows and Kills ) is an essay book in German by Nobel Prize - winning author Herta Müller .
Night Frost is a novel by R. D. Wingfield in the popular series featuring Detective Inspector Jack Frost , coarse , crude , slapdash -- and holder of the George Cross .
The Flying Girl is a novel written by L. Frank Baum , author of the Oz books .
Iron Men and Silver Stars is a collection of western short stories edited by Donald Hamilton .
`` The Tactful Saboteur '' is a novelette by the science fiction author Frank Herbert which first appeared in Galaxy Science Fiction magazine in October 1964 .
Face Forward is a cosmetics book written by Kevyn Aucoin .
The New Machiavelli is a 1911 novel by H. G. Wells that was serialized in The English Review in 1910 .
Sky Burial is a 2004 novel by Xue Xinran , her second .
Flaws in the Glass is Australian writer Patrick White 's autobiography , published in 1981 .
The Howling is a 1977 horror novel by Gary Brandner .
The Forsyte Saga , first published under that name in 1922 , is a series of three novels and two interludes published between 1906 and 1921 by Nobel Prize - winning English author John Galsworthy .
Dragon 's Rock is a novel for young adults by British author Tim Bowler , first published in 1995 .
The Great Abraham Lincoln Pocket Watch Conspiracy is a historical fiction novel written by Jacopo della Quercia .
False Impression is a mystery novel by English author Jeffrey Archer , first published in February 2005 by Macmillan ( ISBN 1405032553 ) .
Drum - Taps is a collection of poetry by American poet Walt Whitman .
The Beastly Beatitudes of Balthazar B is a 1968 novel by Irish American writer J. P. Donleavy .
A Monster at Christmas is a fantasy horror poem by Thomas Canty .
Aeterni Patris ( ( Of the ) Eternal Father ) was an encyclical issued by Pope Leo XIII in August 1879 .
Wounds of Armenia ( Armenian : Վերք Հայաստանի Verk Hayastani ) is an 1841 historical novel by Khachatur Abovian .
Knot Gneiss is the 34th book of the Xanth series by Piers Anthony
The Plantation was the first novel by Chris Kuzneski .
`` The Horla '' ( French : Le Horla ) is an 1887 short horror story written in the style of a journal by French writer Guy de Maupassant , after an initial , much shorter version published in the newspaper Gil Blas , October 26 , 1886 .
One from the GHL ( Hebrew : אחד מן הגח``ל ) is a Hebrew poem , later composed as a song , written by Nathan Alterman during the 1948 Arab - Israeli war .
`` The Heart of the Serpent '' ( Originally in Latin : Cor Serpentis , Russian : Сердце Змеи ) is a 1958 science fiction short story by the Soviet writer and paleontologist Ivan Yefremov .
Memories with Food at Gipsy House is a collection of anecdotes and recipes by Roald Dahl and his second wife , Felicity .
Act of Providence is a supernatural detective novella by Joseph Payne Brennan and Donald M. Grant .
Dimiter ( 2010 ) ( also released under the title The Redemption in various parts of the world ) is a novel by William Peter Blatty , released on March 16 , 2010 through Forge Books .
The Good Earth is a novel by Pearl S. Buck published in 1931 and awarded the Pulitzer Prize for the Novel in 1932 .
Life Studies is the fourth book of poems by Robert Lowell .
Brave New World is a novel written in 1931 by Aldous Huxley and published in 1932 .
On Revolution is a 1963 book by political theorist Hannah Arendt .
Thinking , Fast and Slow is a best - selling 2011 book by Nobel Memorial Prize in Economics winner Daniel Kahneman which summarizes research that he conducted over decades , often in collaboration with Amos Tversky .
The Monkey and the Tiger book pairs two unrelated short gong'an detective novels written by Robert van Gulik and set in Imperial China ( roughly speaking the Tang Dynasty ) .
Never Look Away is the eighth novel by Canadian author Linwood Barclay .
A Lume Spento ( translated by the author as With Tapers Quenched ) is a 1908 poetry collection by Ezra Pound .
The Day of the Bomb ( in German Sadako Will Leben , meaning Sadako Wants to Live ) is a non - fiction book written by the Austrian author Karl Bruckner in 1961 .
Love All is the first novel by the journalist , writer and artist Molly Parkin .
Bright 's Passage is the debut novel by singer / songwriter Josh Ritter .
Tale of the Tribe was a book to be written by Robert Anton Wilson .
The Rationalists is a 1988 book by John Cottingham .
The Unfortunate Traveller : or , the Life of Jack Wilton ( published The Unfortunate Traueller : or , The Life of Iacke Wilton ) by Thomas Nashe ( 1594 ) is a picaresque novel set during the reign of Henry VIII of England .
The Notion Club Papers is the title of an abandoned novel by J. R. R. Tolkien , written during 1945 and published posthumously in Sauron Defeated , the 9th volume of The History of Middle - earth .
The Ghost from the Grand Banks is a 1990 science fiction novel written by Arthur C. Clarke ( ISBN 0 - 575 - 04906 - 5 ) .
The Virtu ( 2006 ) is a fantasy novel by Sarah Monette .
For the Liberation of Brazil is a Marxist tract on guerrilla warfare written by Carlos Marighella .
The Plant is an unfinished serial novel published by Stephen King in 1982 - -85 privately and in 2000 as a commercial e - book .
Between Shades of Gray , a New York Times Bestseller , is the debut novel of American novelist Ruta Sepetys .
`` Moxon 's Master '' is a short story by the late 19th - century American author Ambrose Bierce that speculates on the nature of life and intelligence .
The book was written by Samuel Hahnemann and published in Latin , in two volumes , with the full title Fragmenta de viribus medicamentorum : positivis sive in sano corpore humano observatis ( Fragmentary Observations relative to the Positive Powers of Medicines on the healthy Human Body ) .
Shutterbug Follies is a graphic novel created by Jason Little .
Sonnet 98 is one of 154 sonnets written by the English playwright and poet William Shakespeare .
A Modern Utopia is a 1905 novel by H. G. Wells .
Singin ' and Swingin ' and Gettin ' Merry Like Christmas is the third book of Maya Angelou 's seven - volume autobiography series .
Morvern Callar was the debut novel by Scottish author Alan Warner , first published in 1995 .
The Billions of Arsène Lupin is a detective novel by Maurice Leblanc about gentleman thief Arsène Lupin .
The Siege of Numantia ( Spanish : El cerco de Numancia ) is a tragedy by Miguel de Cervantes set at the siege of Numantia .
The World Without Us is a non - fiction book about what would happen to the natural and built environment if humans suddenly disappeared , written by American journalist Alan Weisman and published by St. Martin 's Thomas Dunne Books .
The Silly Book is a children 's book by Stoo Hample , first published in 1961 and reissued in 2004 .
The Doomsday Conspiracy is a thriller novel by American writer Sidney Sheldon published in 1991 .
The Disruption of American Democracy is a book published by American historian Roy Franklin Nichols in 1948 , which won the 1949 Pulitzer Prize for History .
The Truth Machine ( 1996 ) is a science fiction novel by James L. Halperin about a genius who invents an infallible lie detector .
The Post Office Girl ( German : Rausch der Verwandlung , which roughly means The Intoxication of Transformation ) is a novel by the Austrian writer Stefan Zweig .
The Story of Martha is a BBC Books original novel written by Dan Abnett with David Roden , Steve Lockley & Paul Lewis , Robert Shearman and Simon Jowett and based on the long running science fiction television series Doctor Who .
The General Danced at Dawn is a collection of short stories by George MacDonald Fraser , published first during 1970 and featuring a young Scottish lieutenant named Dand MacNeill .
The Cleft ( 2007 ) is a novel by Doris Lessing .
Double Star is a science fiction novel by Robert A. Heinlein , first serialized in Astounding Science Fiction ( February , March , April 1956 ) and published in hardcover the same year .
The Ideological Origins of the American Revolution is a 1968 Pulitzer Prize - winning book of history by Bernard Bailyn .
The Tale of Ginger and Pickles ( originally , Ginger and Pickles ) is a children 's book written and illustrated by Beatrix Potter , and first published by Frederick Warne & Co. in 1909 .
The Dream of a Lifetime is a 2002 Donald Duck comic by Don Rosa .
Consciousness Explained is a 1991 book by the American philosopher Daniel Dennett which offers an account of how consciousness arises from interaction of physical and cognitive processes in the brain .
The Incandescent Ones is a science fiction novel by astrophysicist Fred Hoyle and his son Geoffrey Hoyle .
The 65 Lakh Heist is first English version ( translated by Sudarshan Purohit ) of a Surender Mohan Pathak book .
An Imperative Duty is a short realist novel by William Dean Howells published in 1891 .
A Good School is a novel by Richard Yates first published in 1978 .
`` The Tyger '' is a poem by the English poet William Blake published in 1794 as part of the Songs of Experience collection .
The Third God is a 2009 fantasy novel by Ricardo Pinto .
Among the Barons is a 2003 book by Margaret Peterson Haddix , about a time in which drastic measures have been taken to quell overpopulation .
The Rime of the Ancient Mariner ( originally The Rime of the Ancyent Marinere ) is the longest major poem by the English poet Samuel Taylor Coleridge , written in 1797 - -98 and published in 1798 in the first edition of Lyrical Ballads .
History of the DC Universe is a two - issue comic book limited series created by Marv Wolfman and George Pérez , and published by DC Comics following the end of Crisis on Infinite Earths .
The Minstrelsy of the Scottish Border is a collection of Border ballads compiled by Walter Scott , first published in three volumes in 1802 and 1803 .
Twilight Comes Twice is a children 's book of free verse written by Ralph Fletcher and illustrated by Kate Kiesler .
The Alexandria Link is Steve Berry 's fifth published novel and was released in 2007 .
A New Lease of Death is a novel by British writer Ruth Rendell , first published in 1967 .
What Technology Wants is a 2010 nonfiction book by Kevin Kelly focused on technology as an extension of life .
The Currents of Space ( 1952 ) is a science fiction novel by the American writer Isaac Asimov .
The Famished Road is the Booker Prize - winning novel written by Nigerian author Ben Okri .
The Faerie Wars Chronicles is a fantasy action young adult novel series written by James Herbert Brennan .
Worlds is a collection of science fiction and fantasy short stories by Eric Flint .
Jih - chi chiu - chung ( Nine Diaries ) was the most popular book published by Chinese writer Yu Dafu .
The Sea - Wolf is a 1904 psychological adventure novel by American novelist Jack London .
The Tuloriad is a novel by John Ringo and Tom Kratman , as part of the Legacy of the Aldenata series .
The Epistula ad Carpianum ( Letter to Carpian ) or Letter of Eusebius is the title traditionally given to a letter from Eusebius of Caesarea to a Christian named Carpianus .
Goodbye Tsugumi ( TUGUMI ) is a novel written by Japanese author Banana Yoshimoto ( 吉本ばなな)in 1989 and translated into English in 2002 by Michael Emmerich .
Sonechka is a novella and collection of short stories by Russian writer Lyudmila Ulitskaya .
Talley & Son is a play by Lanford Wilson , the third in his trilogy focusing on the Talley family of Lebanon , Missouri .
The Fractal Prince is the second science fiction novel by Hannu Rajaniemi and the second novel to feature the post - human gentleman thief Jean le Flambeur .
Goggle - Eyes , or My War with Goggle - Eyes in the U.S. , is a children 's novel by Anne Fine , published by Hamilton in 1989 .
Summer of Secrets is the second part of 21st century Austen series by Rosie Rushton .
A Treatise on Electricity and Magnetism is a two - volume treatise on electromagnetism written by James Clerk Maxwell in 1873 .
Penrod and Sam is a novel by Booth Tarkington that was first published in 1916 .
The Hydrofoil Mystery was written in 2003 by Canadian author Eric Walters .
Caramelo is a 2002 novel by American author Sandra Cisneros .
The Last Centurion is a 2008 stand - alone novel by John Ringo .
Princess of Gossip is a Young Adult novel by Sabrina Bryan ( The Cheetah Girls , Dancing with the Stars ) and Julia DeVillers ( How My Private , Personal Journal Became A Bestseller ) .
Malpertuis ( 1943 ) is a gothic horror novel by the Belgian author Jean Ray ( 1887 - -1964 ) .
Kay the Left - Handed is a historical novel by Leslie Barringer set in twelfth century England .
Asterix and the Actress is the 31st volume of the Asterix comic book series , written and illustrated by Albert Uderzo .
Rome Burning is the second book of Sophia McDougall 's trilogy , following her debut novel , Romanitas , set in a world where the Roman Empire has survived to contemporary times .
La Fausse Suivante , or Le Fourbe Puni is a play by French playwright Pierre de Marivaux written in 1724 , and produced for the first time by the Comédie - Italienneon the July 8 1724 at the theatre of the Hôtel de Bourgogne .
The Autobiography of Malcolm X was published in 1965 , the result of a collaboration between human rights activist Malcolm X and journalist Alex Haley .
The Year of Freaking Out is a 1997 Australian young adult novel by Sarah Walker about 17-year - old Kim , her relationship with her childhood friend Matthew and her passionate friendship with the new girl at school , Rachel .
The Art of Thinking Clearly is a 2013 book by bestselling Swiss writer Rolf Dobelli which describes in short chapters 99 of the most common thinking errors - ranging from cognitive biases to elements like envy and social distortions .
The Man Who Tasted Shapes is a book by neurologist Richard Cytowic about synesthesia .
The Riders is a novel by Australian author Tim Winton published in 1994 .
Conversations with Professor Y ( French : Entretiens avec le professeur Y ) is a 1955 novel by the French writer Louis - Ferdinand Céline .
The Confidential Agent ( 1939 ) is a thriller novel by British author Graham Greene .
The Phantom of the Card Table is a manuscript published in 1931 by Eddie McGuire on the card skills and techniques of Walter Irving Scott aka ' The Phantom ' .
A Philosophical View of Reform is a major prose work by Percy Bysshe Shelley written in 1819 - 20 and first published in 1920 by Oxford University Press .
The Mayor of Castro Street is a 1982 book about Harvey Milk by Randy Shilts .
A History of Western Philosophy is a 1945 book by philosopher Bertrand Russell .
Lady Inger of Ostrat ( original title : Fru Inger til Østeraad ) is a play by Henrik Ibsen , inspired by the life of Inger , Lady of Austraat .
The Loser is a novel by Thomas Bernhard , originally published in German in 1983 .
Deepwater Black is a 1995 novel , first in the Deepwater trilogy , by the New Zealand science fiction writer Ken Catran , where a cast of young characters are supposedly stranded in space while a virus ravages Earth .
Las armas secretas ( translates to The Secret Weapons in English ) is a book of five short stories written by Julio Cortázar .
Montcalm and Wolfe ( ISBN 0 - 306 - 80621 - 5 ) is the sixth volume in Francis Parkman 's seven - volume history , France and England in North America , originally published in 1884 .
Did You Ever Have a Family is the debut novel by American literary agent and author Bill Clegg , published in 2015 .
Les clefs de babel ( literally The keys of Babel ) is a French language children 's novel written by Carina Rozenfeld .
Upland Outlaws is a fantasy novel by Dave Duncan , following The Cutting Edge .
Talking God is the ninth crime fiction novel in the Joe Leaphorn / Jim Chee Navajo Tribal Police series by Tony Hillerman published in 1989 .
`` Down at the Dinghy '' is a short story by J. D. Salinger , originally published in Harper 's in April 1949 , and included in the compilation , Nine Stories .
King of the Wind is a novel by Marguerite Henry that won the Newbery Medal for excellence in American children 's literature in 1949 .
The Skin of Our Teeth is a play by Thornton Wilder which won the Pulitzer Prize for Drama .
He claims Gardner Fox 's dreams were tuned into Earth - Two , explaining their depiction as a fictional world in earlier Barry Allen stories .
Grab Hands and Run is a fictional adaptation of a true story written by Frances Temple .
On Social Freedom : or the Necessary Limits of Individual Freedom Arising Out of the Conditions of Our Social Life is an essay regarding individual and societal freedom initially thought to have been written by the British philosopher John Stuart Mill , but later found to have been falsely attributed to him .
Dansen is a short play by German playwright and dramatist Bertolt Brecht ( 1898 - -1956 ) written in 1939 .
Morning 's Gone is a 2006 novel from Australian author Jon Cleary about Matt Durban , an Australian Labor Party politician who is challenging for his party 's leadership .
Thimble Summer is a novel by Elizabeth Enright that won the 1939 Newbery Medal .
Inside Sahara is a large coffee - table style book containing pictures taken by Basil Pao , who was the stills photographer on the team that made the Sahara with Michael Palin TV program for the BBC .
In the Spirit of Crazy Horse is a book by Peter Matthiessen which chronicles `` The story of Leonard Peltier and the FBI 's war on the American Indian Movement '' .

Los Restos Indígenas de Pichilemu ( English : The Indigenous Remains of Pichilemu ) was a 1908 book published by Chilean historiographer José Toribio Medina .
As a Driven Leaf is a 1939 novel by Milton Steinberg based on the life of Elisha ben Abuyah Steinberg 's novel wrestles with the 2nd century Jewish struggle to reconcile Rabbinic Judaism both culturally and philosophically with Greek Hellenistic society .
One Winter in Eden is a collection of science fiction and fantasy stories by author Michael Bishop .
Memoria descriptiva sobre Tucumán ( Spanish : Descriptive memoir of Tucumán ) is an Argentine 1834 book of Juan Bautista Alberdi .
My Brother Yves ( French : Mon Frère Yves , 1883 ) is a semi - autobiographical novel by French author Pierre Loti .
The Sky So Big and Black is a science fiction novel by John Barnes that was published in 2002 .
The Aquitaine Progression is a novel by Robert Ludlum originally published in 1984 .
What Happened to Burger 's Daughter or How South African Censorship Works is a 1980 collection of essays by South African novelist Nadine Gordimer and others .
The Richlands is an historical novel by the American writer Agnes Sligh Turnbull ( 1888 - -1982 ) set in a rural village in Westmoreland County , Pennsylvania , thirty miles east of Pittsburgh .
The Historia Brittonum is commonly attributed to Nennius , as some recensions have a preface written in his name .
The Evolution of Calpurnia Tate is a 2009 award winning historical young adult novel by Jacqueline Kelly .
The Invention of Solitude is the debut work of Paul Auster , a memoir published in the year 1982 .
Einstein 's Gift is a play written by Canadian playwright Vern Thiessen in 2003 .
The Ignorance of Blood is the final novel in Robert Wilson 's Javier Falcón series , set in Seville .
Honour & Other People 's Children is a collection of two short stories - also described as novellas - by Australian writer Helen Garner .
The Art of Electronics , by Paul Horowitz and Winfield Hill , is a popular textbook dealing with analog and digital electronics .
The Inheritance Cycle is a young adult tetralogy of epic fantasy novels written by American author Christopher Paolini .
The Angel Maker 's Wife is Camilla Läckberg 's eighth book in her Fjällbacka series , and was published in Sweden on 19 December 2011 .
The Scheme for Full Employment is a novel by the English author Magnus Mills , published in 2003 by Flamingo .
I Am NOT Going to Get Up Today ! is a children 's book written by Theodor Geisel under the pen name Dr. Seuss and illustrated by James Stevenson and published by Random House on October 12 , 1987 .
Saint Leibowitz and the Wild Horse Woman ( 1997 ) is a science fiction novel written by Walter M. Miller , Jr. It is a follow - up to Miller 's 1959 book A Canticle for Leibowitz .
The Family Book is a 2003 children 's book written by Todd Parr that details the daily lives of all kinds of families .
Murder Twice Told is a collection of two short thrillers by Donald Hamilton .
The Clockwork Girl is an all - ages / science fiction / fantasy comic series created by Sean O’Reilly and Kevin Hanna , that ran for six issues and was published in a collected edition for the first time in 2008 .
Debit and Credit ( German : Soll und Haben , 1855 ) is a novel in six volumes by Gustav Freytag .
Reveries of a Solitary Walker ( or Reveries of the Solitary Walker ; French : Les Rêveries du promeneur solitaire ) is an unfinished book by Genevan philosopher Jean - Jacques Rousseau , written between 1776 and 1778 .

Faux passeports subtitled ' ou les mémoires d'un agitateur ' in its original version , is a Belgian novel by Charles Plisnier .

An Infinite Summer is the second collection of short stories by Christopher Priest and the first of his books to collect stories set in the Dream Archipelago .
`` Maid of Athens , ere we part '' is a poem by Lord Byron , written in 1810 and dedicated to a young girl of Athens .
Madame de La Carlière , sub - titled On the inconsequence of public judgement of our actions , is a fable written by the French writer Denis Diderot in 1772 , and published for the first time in 1798 .
`` A Diamond Guitar '' is a short story by Truman Capote , first published in Harper 's Bazaar in 1950 ; it is noted as one of his better quality early short stories .
Stormrider is a fantasy novel by the author David Gemmell published in 2002 .
The Anatomy of a Moment ( Spanish : Anatomía de un instante ) is a 2009 non - fiction book by Javier Cercas , which won the National Prize for Narrative Writing .
Nemesis Games is a 2015 science fiction novel by James S. A. Corey , the pen name of Daniel Abraham and Ty Franck , and the fifth book in their The Expanse series .
The Adventures of Captain Horn is an 1895 adventure novel by Frank R. Stockton that was the third - best selling book in the United States in 1895 .
Wild Fowl Decoys is an art reference book by American collector Joel Barber , first published in 1934 by Windward House .
The Court of the Air is the first book by Stephen Hunt in his Jackelian series .
Heidi ( pronounced ( ˈhaɪdi ) ) is a work of children 's fiction published in 1881 by Swiss author Johanna Spyri , originally published in two parts as Heidi 's years of learning and travel ( German : Heidis Lehr- und Wanderjahre ) and Heidi makes use of what she has learned .
Billiards at Half - Past Nine ( German : Billard um halb zehn ) is a 1959 novel by the German author Heinrich Böll .
The Miseries of Human Life was written by James Beresford ( 1764 - -1840 ) and published in 1806 , first as a single volume and then as an expanded two - volume edition later that year .
The Seven Messengers ( Italian : I sette messaggeri ) is a collection of short stories written by Dino Buzzati and published as a book in 1942 .
Human Traces is a 2005 novel by Sebastian Faulks , best known as the British author of Birdsong and Charlotte Gray .
Letters Written in France is a series of letters written by English writer Helen Maria Williams , first published in 1790 .
Contes et nouvelles en vers ( English : Tales and Novellas in Verse ) is an anthology of various ribald short stories and novellas collected and versified from prose by Jean de La Fontaine .
Now and Then , Amen is a 1988 novel from Australian author Jon Cleary .
The Height of the Scream is a collection of horror stories by author Ramsey Campbell .
The Religion of Man ( 1931 ) is a compilation of lectures by Rabindranath Tagore , edited by him and drawn largely from his Hibbert Lectures given at Oxford University in May 1930 .
`` The Terrible Old Man '' is a very short short story ( less than 1200 words ) by H. P. Lovecraft , written on January 28 , 1920 , and first published in the Tryout , an amateur press publication , in July 1921 .
Of Nightingales That Weep is a historical novel for children by Katherine Paterson , published by Crowell in 1974 .
Murphy 's Gold is the second novella in Murphy series by Gary Paulsen .
The Machinery of Freedom is a nonfiction book by David D. Friedman which advocates Friedman 's vision of an anarcho - capitalist society .
My Sweet Audrina is a 1982 novel by V. C. Andrews .
The Crow Comes Last ( Italian : Ultimo viene il corvo ) is a short story collection by Italo Calvino published in 1949 .
Withered Murder is the second of the collaborations of Anthony Shaffer and Peter Shaffer under the pseudonym Peter Anthony .
Claude Gueux was a short story written by Victor Hugo in 1834 .
Dead Even is the second novel written by Brad Meltzer about a husband and wife on opposite sides of a legal case .
On the Soul ( Greek Περὶ Ψυχῆς , Perì Psūchês ; Latin De Anima ) is a major treatise by Aristotle on the nature of living things .
Hospital of the Transfiguration ( in Polish : Szpital Przemienienia ) is a book written by Stanisław Lem .
Robopocalypse is a science fiction book by Daniel H. Wilson published in 2011 .
A Complicated Kindness is the third novel by Canadian author Miriam Toews .
The Lost Hero is a 2010 fantasy - adventure novel written by Rick Riordan and is based on Greek and Roman mythology .
La Permission is a 1967 French language novel written by Melvin Van Peebles which was turned into the film , The Story of a Three - Day Pass .
A Horse and Two Goats and Other Stories ( also published as A Horse and Two Goats ) is a collection of short stories by R. K. Narayan , published in 1970 by The Bodley Head .
`` The Man Who Would Not Shake Hands '' is a short story by Stephen King first published in the 1982 horror anthology Shadows 4 , edited by Charles L. Grant , and collected in Skeleton Crew in 1985 .
Second Glance is a fiction novel written by American author Jodi Picoult .
Little Pilgrim ( Korean : 화엄경 ) is a novel by the South Korean writer Ko Un .
The Compendium of Materia Medica , also known by the romanizations Bencao Gangmu or Pen - tsao Kang - mu , is a Chinese materia medica work written by Li Shizhen during the Ming Dynasty .
`` Death of the Poet '' ( Russian : `` Смерть Поэта '' ) is an 1837 poem by Mikhail Lermontov , written in reaction to the death of Alexander Pushkin .
Manna from Heaven is a book that contains a collection of short stories that were written by fantasy and science fiction author Roger Zelazny .
Escape from Mr. Lemoncello 's Library is a children 's novel by author Chris Grabenstein .

The Virgin and the Gypsy is a short story ( or novella ) by English author D. H. Lawrence .
Vandover and the Brute is a novel by Frank Norris , written in 1894 - -5 and first published in 1914 .
Lonesome Places is a collection of fantasy and horror short stories by American author August Derleth .
A Day in Ostrobothnia ( Finnish : Pohjanmaa ) is a 1985 novel by Finnish author Antti Tuuri .
Natural Theology or Evidences of the Existence and Attributes of the Deity is an 1802 work of Christian apologetics and philosophy of religion by the English clergyman William Paley ( July 1743 -- 25 May 1805 ) .
Der fremde Blick oder das Leben ist ein Furz in der Laterne is a book by Nobel Prize - winning author Herta Müller .
Exsul Familia is the apostolic constitution written by Pope Pius XII on the topic of migration .
Europe Central ( 2005 ) is a novel by William T. Vollmann that won the U.S. National Book Award for Fiction .
Knee - Knock Rise is a children 's book written by Natalie Babbitt and published in 1970 .
Eclipse of the Crescent Moon ( Hungarian : Egri csillagok lit . `` Stars of Eger '' ) is a historical novel by the Hungarian writer Géza Gárdonyi .
The Sorrow Gondola ( Swedish : Sorgegondolen ) is a 1996 poetry collection by the Swedish writer Tomas Tranströmer .
Under Plum Lake is a children 's adventure novel by Lionel Davidson , first published in 1980 .
Everything Matters ! ( 2009 ) is American author Ron Currie Jr. 's second novel .
Business Dynamics is a book by John Sterman that applies system dynamics to business .
The Work , Wealth and Happiness of Mankind by H. G. Wells is the final work of a trilogy of which the first volumes were The Outline of History ( 1919 - -1920 ) and The Science of Life ( 1929 ) .
The Witch of Edmonton is an English Jacobean play , written by William Rowley , Thomas Dekker and John Ford in 1621 .
Gold Dust and Ashes is a book by Ion Idriess set in the New Guina goldfields at Bulolo .
Yondering is a collection of short stories by American author Louis L'Amour , published in 1980 .
On My Honor is a short Newbery Honor - winning novel by Marion Dane Bauer , first published in 1986 .
`` Unaccompanied Sonata '' is a short story by Orson Scott Card , first published in the March , 1979 issue of Omni magazine .
Pioneer , Go Home ! is a satirical novel by Richard P. Powell , first published in 1959 .
The Wars is a 1977 novel by Timothy Findley that tells the story of a young Canadian officer in World War I. Nineteen - year - old Robert Ross tries to escape both his grief over his sister 's death and the social norms of oppressive Victorian upper - class society by enlisting in the Great War .
The Righteous Men is a novel written by Sam Bourne , a pseudonym of English journalist Jonathan Freedland .
Into a Strange Lost World is a children fiction novel by Richard Hough under the pen name of Bruce Carter .
Selam Professor Shonku ( Hats off , Professor Shonku ) is a Professor Shonku series book written by Satyajit Ray and published by Ananda Publishers in 1995 .
A Most Wanted Man is a thriller / espionage novel by John le Carré published in September 2008 by Hodder & Stoughton in the United Kingdom and in October 2008 by Scribner in the United States .
A Liar 's Autobiography , Volume VI is a comical autobiography written by Graham Chapman of Monty Python fame , featuring a fictionalised account of his life .
Humlehjertene ( English : The Bumblebee Hearts ) is a novel published in 1980 by the Norwegian writer Ola Bauer .
And Never Said a Word ( German : Und sagte kein einziges Wort ) is a novel by German author Heinrich Böll , published in 1953 .
The Yellow Sound ( in German , Der Gelbe Klang ) is an experimental theater piece originated by the Russian artist Wassily Kandinsky .
Watch and Ward is a short novel by Henry James , first published as a serial in The Atlantic Monthly in 1871 and later as a book in 1878 .
The Hidden Past by Jude Watson is the third in a series of young reader novels called Jedi Apprentice .
7 Stories is a play created by Canadian playwright Morris Panych .
On the Way of Resurrection ( Arabic : فِي سَبِيلِ البعث , Fi Sabil al Baath ) is a political literature book written by Michel Aflaq , one of the founders of Ba'athism .
They Were Strong and Good is a children 's nonfiction book written and illustrated by Robert Lawson , who won the 1941 Caldecott Medal for excellence in illustration of an American children 's picture book .
The Macintosh Way was the first book written by former Apple evangelist Guy Kawasaki .
When Jonathan Died is a novel by Tony Duvert , translated by D.R. Roberts .
Treasures of the Snow is a children 's story book by Patricia St. John .
The Bravo is a novel by James Fenimore Cooper first published in 1831 in three volumes .
The Man Who Laughs ( also published under the title By Order of the King ) is a novel by Victor Hugo , originally published in April 1869 under the French title L'Homme qui rit .
Problems of a Sociology of Knowledge ( German : Probleme einer Soziologie des Wissens ) is a 1924 essay by the German philosopher , sociologist , and anthropologist Max Scheler .
Biancaneve is an Italian erotic comic book , created in 1972 by Renzo Barbieri and Rubino Ventura and illustrated by Leone Frollo .
Terminal Freeze is the fourth solo novel by Lincoln Child .
Phoenix in Obsidian ( alternate title : The Silver Warriors ) is a science fantasy novel by Michael Moorcock .
After Having Spent a Night Among Horses ( Swedish : Efter att ha tillbringat en natt bland hästar ) is a 1998 poetry collection by Finnish poet Tua Forsström .
Selected Stories is a volume of short stories by Alice Munro , published by McClelland and Stewart in 1996 .
Adventures in the Screen Trade is a book about Hollywood written in 1983 by American novelist and screenwriter William Goldman .
Zothique is an imagined future continent in a series of short stories by Clark Ashton Smith .
The Cruelty of the Spaniards in Peru was an innovative 1658 theatrical presentation , a hybrid entertainment or masque or `` operatic show '' , written and produced by Sir William Davenant .
The Divine Legation of Moses is the best - known work of William Warburton , an English theologian of the 18th century who became bishop of Gloucester .

The Final Adventures of Solar Pons is a collection of detective , science fiction short stories by author August Derleth .

Generation Loss is a novel published by Elizabeth Hand .
Davy and the Goblin , or , What Followed Reading `` Alice 's Adventures in Wonderland '' is a novel by Charles E. Carryl that was serialized in St. Nicholas magazine from December 1884 to March 1885 before being published by Houghton Mifflin of Boston and Frederick Warne of London in 1885 .
Alias Grace is a novel of historical fiction by Canadian writer Margaret Atwood .
Sister Alice ( Tor Books , ISBN 0 - 7653 - 0225-X ) is a science fiction novel by author Robert Reed , first published in 2003 .
Soft City is the first book written by Jonathan Raban , and published by The Harvill Press in 1974 .

The Art of Keeping Cool is a children 's historical fiction book by Janet Taylor Lisle published in October 2000 by Anthem Books .
The Twilight Tomb was published in September 2006 , and was written by Greg A. Vaughan , with cover art by Jon Foster and interior art by Marvin Mariano and Steve Prescott .
The Quantum Rose is a science fiction novel by Catherine Asaro which tells the story of Kamoj Argali and Skolian Prince Havyrl Valdoria .
The Ugly Swans ( Russian : Гадкие лебеди ) is a science fiction novel by Arkady and Boris Strugatsky .
A Berlin Republic ( German : Die Normalität einer Berliner Republik . Kleine Politische Schriften VIII ) is a 1997 book composed of a collection of transcripts of interviews with the German philosopher and sociologist Jürgen Habermas conducted by various European media in the mid-1990s .
L'enfant penchée ( literally , The Leaning Child ) is a graphic novel by Belgian comic artists François Schuiten and Benoît Peeters , the sixth volume of their ongoing Les Cités Obscures series .
Ellison Wonderland is a collection of short stories by author Harlan Ellison that was originally published in 1962 .
Strait Is the Gate ( French : La Porte Étroite ) is a 1909 French novel written by André Gide .

Erik Axel Karlfeldt ( 20 July 1864 -- 8 April 1931 ) was a Swedish poet whose highly symbolist poetry masquerading as regionalism was popular and won him the Nobel Prize in Literature posthumously in 1931 after he had been nominated by Nathan Söderblom , member of the Swedish Academy .
In the same year Harry Ashmore won the Pulitzer Prize for Editorial Writing , For the forcefulness , dispassionate analysis and clarity of his editorials on the school integration conflict in Little Rock .

Albert Celerin ( 8 September 1912 -- 31 December 1997 ) was a German Luftwaffe Reconnaissance pilot and recipient of the Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross during World War II . The Knight 's Cross of the Iron Cross was awarded to recognise extreme battlefield bravery or successful military leadership .

A Very Merry Daughter of the Bride is a 2008 television movie starring Joanna García and Luke Perry .
Lecointe Island is an elongated island , 7.27 km ( 4.52 mi ) long between Cape Kaiser and Hvarchil Point , 2.2 km ( 1.4 mi ) wide and 700 m ( 2,300 ft ) high , separated from the east coast of Brabant Island by Pampa Passage , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Howard Glacier ( 77 ° 41′S 163 ° 5′E ) is a small alpine glacier just west of Crescent Glacier , flowing into Taylor Valley on the north from the Kukri Hills , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Law - Racoviță Station ( Romanian : Stația Law - Racoviță ) is the first permanent Romanian station for research and exploration in Antarctica , named after the Romanian explorer Emil Racoviță and inaugurated on January 13 , 2006 at the location of a station constructed in 1986 by Australia and donated to Romania .
Mount Blair ( 72 ° 32′S 160 ° 49′E ) is a small but conspicuous mountain , 2,120 metres ( 6,960 ft ) high , standing 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) northwest of Mount Weihaupt in the Outback Nunataks , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
McCarthy Glacier ( 86 ° 4′S 127 ° 24′W ) is a broad glacier at the south side of Wisconsin Plateau , Antarctica , flowing west to merge with the lower part of Olentangy Glacier before entering Reedy Glacier just southwest of Mount McNaughton .
Knobhead Moraine ( 77 ° 51′S 161 ° 38′E ) is a conspicuous moraine of large boulders to the north of Knobhead , Quartermain Mountains , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Fry Glacier ( 76 ° 38′S 162 ° 18′E ) is a glacier draining the slopes at the northeast corner of the Convoy Range and flowing along the south end of the Kirkwood Range into Tripp Bay , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Lister is a massive mountain , 4,025 metres ( 13,200 ft ) high , forming the highest point in the Royal Society Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Mervyn ( 70 ° 31′S 65 ° 13′E ) is a very sharp peak standing south of the main body of the Porthos Range in the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica , about 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) south of Mount Kirkby .
Dike Cirque ( 83 ° 14′S 157 ° 57′E ) is a semi - circular glacial cirque 1 nautical mile ( 2 km ) wide in the Miller Range of Antarctica .
Zed Islands is a small group of islands , the westernmost rising to 290 m ( 951 ft ) , lying off the northeast extremity of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica comprising four islands :
Mawson Bank ( 73 ° 30′S 174 ° 0′E ) is a submarine bank in the Ross Sea off Antarctica named for British Antarctic scientist Sir Douglas Mawson .
Mount Kathleen ( 83 ° 46′S 172 ° 48′E ) is a peak about 900 metres ( 3,000 ft ) high , being the central and highest summit of Ebony Ridge at the north end of the Commonwealth Range , Antarctica .
Provadiya Hook ( Provadiyska Kosa \pro - va-'diy - ska ko-'sa\ ) is a gravel barrier spit separating the inner Yankee Harbour in Greenwich Island , Antarctica from the outer Shopski Cove and McFarlane Strait .
Mount Kliment Ohridski ( Vrah Kliment Ohridski \'vr&h ' kli - ment ' o - hrid - ski\ ) is the highest ridge ( 1500 m ) in the Sofia University Mountains on Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Kenfield Nunatak ( 73 ° 46′S 99 ° 3′W ) is an isolated nunatak which lies about 8 nautical miles ( 15 km ) southeast of the head of Cosgrove Ice Shelf and 17 nautical miles ( 31 km ) east - northeast of Pryor Cliff , at the extreme northern end of the Hudson Mountains , Antarctica .
Sullivan Glacier ( 69 ° 42′S 70 ° 45′W ) is a glacier flowing west into Gilbert Glacier , immediately south of Elgar Uplands in the north part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Ebony Wall ( 63 ° 55′S 59 ° 9′W ) is a dark , nearly vertical rock wall in Antarctica , which rises about 400 metres ( 1,300 ft ) at the head of Pettus Glacier .
Chapman Rocks is a group of rocks in central Hero Bay on the north side of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Harris Ledge ( 77 ° 28′S 161 ° 26′E ) is a flat , ice - free ridge to the north of Mount Hercules in the Olympus Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Krieger Peak ( 71 ° 46′S 70 ° 35′W ) is a peak between Duffy Peak and The Obelisk in the central part of the Staccato Peaks , southern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Pavlikeni Point ( Nos Pavlikeni \'nos pa - vli-'ke - ni\ ) projects 600 m from the north coast of Greenwich Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and is snow - free in summer .
Mount Exley ( 81 ° 10′S 156 ° 14′E ) is a mountain at 1,980 metres ( 6,500 ft ) in the Wallabies Nunataks , west of the Churchill Mountains of Antarctica .
Brazil ( i / brəˈzɪl/ ; Portuguese : Brasil ( bɾaˈziw ) ) , officially the Federative Republic of Brazil ( Portuguese : República Federativa do Brasil , listen ) , is the largest country in both South America and the Latin American region .
Libois Bay ( 65 ° 4′S 64 ° 3′W ) is a cove on the west side of Cholet Island which is entered between Rozo Point , the northwest end of Cholet Island , and Paumelle Point , the northwest end of Booth Island , in the Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .
Mills Cliff ( 72 ° 10′S 95 ° 53′W ) is an isolated rock cliff in the north - central part of Lofgren Peninsula , Thurston Island , Antarctica .
Hero Inlet ( 64 ° 46′S 64 ° 4′W ) is a narrow inlet at the south side of Palmer Station between Gamage Point and Bonaparte Point , along the southwest side of Anvers Island in Antarctica .
Gjertsen Promontory ( 86 ° 38′S 148 ° 32′W ) is a low but sharply rising promontory at the extremity of the spur trending north from Mount Gjertsen , in the La Gorce Mountains of Antarctica .
Mims Spur ( 86 ° 2′S 125 ° 35′W ) is a prominent rock spur protruding from the southern extremity of Wisconsin Plateau , Antarctica , situated just southeast of Polygon Spur on the north side of McCarthy Glacier .
Mount Menzies is the culminating peak ( 3,355 m ; 11,007 ft ) on the large massif between Mount Mather and Mount Bayliss , standing on the south side of Fisher Glacier , Antarctica .
Armstrong Reef is a reef that encompasses a large number of ice - free plutonic islets and rocks , extending for 9 km ( 6 mi ) from the south - west end of Renaud Island , in the Biscoe Islands of Antarctica .
Endurance Glacier is a broad glacier north of Mount Elder , draining south - east to the south coast of Elephant Island in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica , and is the main discharge glacier on the island .
Inner Crater ( 77 ° 32′S 167 ° 10′E ) is the topographic feature that embraces the crater within the floor of Main Crater , at the summit of Mount Erebus , Ross Island , Antarctica .
Hobbs Point ( 64 ° 37′S 62 ° 3′W ) is the northeastern end of Brooklyn Island in Wilhelmina Bay , off the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Kosovo ( /ˈkɒsəvoʊ , ˈkoʊ-/ ; Albanian : Kosova ; Serbian Cyrillic : Косово ) is a disputed territory and partially recognised state in Southeastern Europe that declared its independence from Serbia in February 2008 as the Republic of Kosovo .
Scott Island is a small uninhabited island of volcanic origin in the Ross Sea , Southern Ocean , 505 kilometres ( 310 mi ) northeast of Cape Adare , the northeastern extremity of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Allison Ridge ( 70 ° 45′S 66 ° 19′E ) is a rock ridge , partly snow - covered , about 0.5 nautical miles ( 1 km ) west of Mount Bunt in the Aramis Range , Prince Charles Mountains , Antarctica .
The Harrisson Ice Rises ( 66 ° 27′S 96 ° 39′E ) are a local swelling of the ice surface 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) west - southwest of Henderson Island , Antarctica , where the Shackleton Ice Shelf overrides an underlying obstruction .
Harmony Point is a point which lies close west of Harmony Cove and forms the western extremity of Nelson Island , in the South Shetland Islands of Antarctica .
Hurley Glacier ( 67 ° 34′S 68 ° 32′W ) is a glacier between Mount Gaudry and Mount Liotard , flowing east into Ryder Bay , Adelaide Island , Antarctica .
Fivemile Rock ( 63 ° 29′S 57 ° 3′W ) is a small nunatak , 375 metres ( 1,230 ft ) high , rising just northwest of Mineral Hill on Tabarin Peninsula , Antarctica .
Higgins Canyon ( 84 ° 47′S 114 ° 41′W ) is a steep - sided , ice - filled canyon immediately east of Schulthess Buttress , on the north side of Buckeye Table in the Ohio Range of the Horlick Mountains in Antarctica .
Lavoisier Island is an island 29 km ( 18 mi ) long and 8 km ( 5 mi ) wide , lying between Rabot and Watkins Islands in the Biscoe Islands , Antarctica .
Rundvågs Head ( 69 ° 53′S 39 ° 0′E ) , in Antarctica , is a rock headland rising to 160 metres ( 520 ft ) at the southwest margin of Rundvåg Bay , on the southeast coast of Lutzow - Holm Bay .
Rainbow Ridge ( 78 ° 6′S 165 ° 24′E ) is a small ridge which forms a distinct western rim to the large crater - like depression high in the central part of Brown Peninsula , in Victoria Land in Antarctica .

King Edward VII Land or King Edward VII Peninsula is a large , ice - covered peninsula which forms the northwestern extremity of Marie Byrd Land in Antarctica .
The Helo Cliffs ( 77 ° 30′S 167 ° 7′E ) are a set of prominent cliffs at about 3,525 metres ( 11,565 ft ) on the north rim of the summit caldera of Mount Erebus , on Ross Island , Antarctica .

Guyatt Ridge ( 80 ° 38′S 29 ° 27′W ) is a ridge southwest of Wedge Ridge in the southern part of the Haskard Highlands , in the Shackleton Range , Antarctica .
Kessler Peak ( 83 ° 37′S 167 ° 50′E ) is a conspicuous cone - shaped peak , 2,180 metres ( 7,150 ft ) high , in the Queen Alexandra Range of Antarctica , standing at the east side of Lennox - King Glacier , 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) west - southwest of Mount Rotolante .
Mount Hartkopf is a mountain , 1,110 metres ( 3,640 ft ) high , rising along the east side of the upper reaches of Land Glacier , 11 nautical miles ( 20 km ) southeast of Mount McCoy , in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Herring Point ( Bulgarian : нос Херинг , `` Nos Herring '' \'nos ' he - ring\ ) is a point on the north coast of Rugged Island off the west coast of Byers Peninsula of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica forming the east side of the entrance to Hersilia Cove .

The Auriga Nunataks ( 70 ° 42′S 66 ° 38′W ) are a small group of nunataks in Palmer Land , Antarctica , located 21 miles ( 34 km ) east of Wade Point at the head of Bertram Glacier .

Black Glacier ( 71 ° 40′S 164 ° 42′E ) is a broad tributary to the Lillie Glacier flowing northeast , marking the southeast extent of the Bowers Mountains , a major mountain range situated in the geographical location of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Coppermine Peninsula is the 1.7 km long , 500 m wide and rising to 105 m rugged rocky promontory forming the northwest extremity of Alfatar Peninsula and Robert Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica and lying between English Strait to the west and Carlota Cove to the east .
Hesperides Hill ( Halm Hesperides \'h&lm he - spe-'ri - des\ ) is a ridge linked by a saddle of elevation 52 m with the northern slopes of Atlantic Club Ridge on Hurd Peninsula , eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Vetrov Hill ( 66 ° 34′S 92 ° 58′E ) is a hill rising to 20 m , standing at the east side of the entrance to McDonald Bay on the coast of Antarctica .
Krout Glacier ( 84 ° 53′S 172 ° 12′W ) is a tributary glacier , 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) long , draining the north slopes of the Prince Olav Mountains , Antarctica , between Mount Sellery and Mount Smithson and entering Gough Glacier just east of Mount Dodge .
Dragon Beach ( 62 ° 28′S 60 ° 8′W ) is a broad gravel and bounder strewn area flanking Dragon Cove , and extending up to about 10 metres ( 33 ft ) above sea level on Varna Peninsula , Livingston Island in Antarctica .
The Gruvleflesa Knolls ( 71 ° 44′S 8 ° 50′E ) are two low rock knolls rising above the glacial moraine just west of the Gruvletindane Crags , in the Kurze Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .

The Haslam Heights ( 67 ° 25′S 67 ° 30′W ) are a line of peaks trending north - northeast -- south - southwest , rising to about 1,000 metres ( 3,300 ft ) to the west of Vallot Glacier and Nye Glacier in Arrowsmith Peninsula , Graham Land , Antarctica .
Austskjera is a group of rocks ( skerries ) in Antarctica , lying close to the coast about 9 kilometres ( 5 nmi ) east of Cape Daly , 4 kilometres ( 2 nmi ) east - southeast of Safety Island , and 3 kilometres ( 1.5 nmi ) east - southeast of Landmark Point .

Mill Glacier is a tributary glacier , 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) wide , flowing northwest between the Dominion Range and the Supporters Range into Beardmore Glacier , Antarctica .
Marshall Valley ( 78 ° 4′S 164 ° 12′E ) is a small valley in Antarctica , ice free except for Rivard Glacier at its western head .
McLin Glacier ( 71 ° 12′S 163 ° 27′E ) is a tributary glacier which flows north of McKenzie Nunatak into Graveson Glacier , in the Bowers Mountains of Antarctica .
Knezevich Rock ( 76 ° 10′S 112 ° 0′W ) is a rock outcrop on the lower part of the north slope of Mount Takahe in Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .

Mount Kendrick ( 86 ° 22′S 156 ° 40′W ) is a massive ice - covered mountain , 3,610 metres ( 11,840 ft ) high , surmounting the east side of the Nilsen Plateau at the head of Bartlett Glacier , in the Queen Maud Mountains of Antarctica .

German submarine U-517 was a Type IXC U - boat of the Nazi Germany 's Kriegsmarine during World War II . She was laid down at the Deutsche Werft in Hamburg as yard number 313 on 24 September 1940 , launched on 30 December 1941 and commissioned on 21 March 1942 with Kapitänleutnant Paul Hartwig in command .

The Memorial to the Great Exhibition is an outdoor monument commemorating the Great Exhibition ( 1851 ) and depicting Albert , Prince Consort , designed by Joseph Durham with modifications by Sydney Smirke and located south of Royal Albert Hall in London , United Kingdom .
The Submission of Prince Dipo Negoro to General De Kock ( Dutch : De onderwerping van Diepo Negoro aan luitenant - generaal baron De Kock ) is an oil painting on canvas painted by Nicolaas Pieneman between 1830 and 1835 .
Object ( Le Déjeuner en fourrure ) , lit . Object ( `` The Luncheon in Fur '' ) , known in English as Fur Breakfast or Breakfast in Fur , is a 1936 sculpture by the surrealist Méret Oppenheim , consisting of a fur - covered teacup , saucer and spoon .
A Year in the Life is a 1986 miniseries and a one - hour dramatic series that ran on NBC during the 1987 - -1988 television season , created by Joshua Brand and John Falsey .
Eban Goodstein ( born 1960 ) is an economist , author , and public educator who directs both the Center for Environmental Policy and the MBA in Sustainability at Bard College .
Pádraic Ó Neachtain ( born 1973 ) is an Irish television presenter , director , and journalist .
Jan - Ove Palmberg , born 1943 , is a Professor of Mechanical Engineering at Linköping University .
Deskin Green ( 1847 - -1918 ) was an American politician who , from 1908 to 1910 , served as a member of the Virginia House of Delegates , representing the counties of Tazewell and Buchanan .
Thomas Ashwell or Ashewell ( c. 1478 -- after 1513 ( possibly 1527 ? ) ) was an English composer of the Renaissance .
Hortensia Fussy ( born 25 March 1954 in Graz ; pseudonym : Hortensia ) , is an Austrian sculptor .
Aarón Piña Mora ( 1914 - -2010 ) was a Mexican painter and muralist .
Chakir Boujattaoui ( born 16 January 1983 in Nador ) is a Moroccan is a long distance runner who specialises in cross country running , and the 5000 metres and steeplechase on the track .
Marcus Barlow ( 1890 - -1954 ) was an Australian architect and a successful and influential designer during the economic turmoil of The Great Depression and World War II . His projects were important to the development of Melbourne architecture , being innovative in use of new technologies and inspired by international design movements .
Leul Ras Mengesha Seyoum ( Ge'ez : መንገሻ ሰዩም ) GCVO ( born 7 December 1927 ) is a member of the imperial family of the Ethiopian Empire .

Peter Pett , ( 6 August 1610 -- ? 1672 ) was an English Master Shipwright , and Second Resident Commissioner of Chatham Dockyard .
Faezeh Hashemi Bahramani , more known as Faezeh Hashemi Rafsanjani ( Persian : فائزه هاشمی رفسنجانی‎ ; born 7 January 1962 ) is an Iranian Women 's rights activist , politician and former journalist who served as a member of Iranian parliament from 1996 to 2000 .
Anna Giordano ( born in 1965 ) is an Italian conservationist .
Nima Aziminejad ( Persian : نیما عظیمی‌نژاد‎ ) , ( born 15 September 1978 ) is an Iranian composer , setar player and sound engineer .
Roman Dostál ( pronounced ( ˈroman ˈdostaːl ) ; born 13 July 1970 ) is a former Czech biathlete .

Emomo Eddy Ngoyi ( born 13 October 1993 ) is a Congolese international footballer who plays as a striker for Shark XI FC Kinshasa in DR Congo .
Moniek Nijhuis ( born 20 March 1988 ) is a Dutch swimmer who specializes in breaststroke .
Karel Vinck ( born 19 September 1938 , Aalst ) is a Belgian businessman .
Grace Sturtevant ( 1865 - -1947 ) was an early 20th century iris breeder who has been called `` America 's first lady of iris '' .
Henryk Kierzkowski ( born 10 October 1943 ) is a Polish economist known for his work on imperfect competition and international trade .
Lisa Sousa ( born 1962 ) is an American academic historian active in the field of Latin American studies .
General Sir Harry Aubrey de Vere Maclean ( Kaïd ) KCMG ( 1848 - -1920 ) was a Scottish soldier , and instructor to the Moroccan Army .
George Brydges , 6th Baron Chandos ( 1620 - -1655 ) was a supporter of Charles I of England during his struggle with Parliament , and distinguished himself at the first Battle of Newbury in 1643 .
Andrée Ferretti ( born in 1935 ) is a Canadian political figure and author .
Major General Sir Frank Kingsley Norris KBE CB DSO ED ( 25 June 1893 -- 1 May 1984 ) was an Australian military officer and physician .
Juan Carlos Giordano ( born c. 1961 ) is an activist in Socialist Left ( Argentina ) .
Inga Peulich ( born 15 October 1956 ) is an Australian politician currently serving in the Legislative Council in the Parliament of Victoria as Member for the South Eastern Metropolitan Region .
Tekin Bingöl ( born 1 August 1955 ) is a Turkish politician who serves as the Deputy Leader of the Republican People 's Party responsible for political organisation since 8 May 2014 .
Akbaruddin Owaisi ( born 14 June 1970 ) is a politician based in Hyderabad , Telangana and an MLA of the Telangana Legislative Assembly .
Sean de Silva ( born 17 January 1990 ) is a Trinidadian international footballer who currently plays for and captains Central FC in the TT Pro League .
S. Muthiah Mudaliar CIE ( 1883 - July 15 , 1953 ) was an Indian politician and legislator of the Justice Party and later , the Swarajya Party and an independent minister in the Madras Presidency .
Fatma Ekenoğlu ( born in Paphos in 1956 ) is a Turkish Cypriot politician .
David Atherton OBE , ( born 3 January 1944 ) is an English conductor and co - founder of the London Sinfonietta .
Mikael Mikael ( * 1974 ) is a German artist .
Djamaluddin Malik ( 13 February 1917 -- 8 June 1970 ) was a prominent Indonesian film producer , politician , entrepreneur .
Toshinori Ishikuma ( born September 1950 ) is a Japanese psychology professor known for his work on introducing and establishing the system of school psychology services in Japan .
Gustav Bychowski ( born 1895 in Warsaw , Poland , died April 3 , 1972 in Fes , Morocco ) was an American psychiatrist , psychoanalyst and author .
Harry Forbes Witherby , MBE , FZS , MBOU ( 7 October 1873 - 11 December 1943 ( aged 70 ) ) was a noted British ornithologist , author , publisher and founding editor ( in 1907 ) of the magazine British Birds .
Tomás Romañach ( born 1890 - death date unknown ) was a Cuban baseball shortstop in the Cuban League and Negro leagues .
Veronica Lazăr ( 16 October 1938 - 8 June 2014 ) was a Romanian born Italian actress .
Shota Abkhazava ( Russian : Шота Абхазава , born 12 August 1971 ) is a racing driver , race cars designer , a businessman , an owner of two race circuits in Russia and Georgia .
Vladimir Bodnar is born in Staraya Ushitsa , Kamenets - Podolsk region of Ukraine on December 26 , 1942 .
Sir Geoffrey le Scrope ( 1285 -- 2 December 1340 ) was an English lawyer , and Chief Justice of the King 's Bench for four periods between 1324 and 1338 .

Noor Muhammad ( 15 April 1951 -- 12 April 2004 ) was a notable Pakistani mathematician and mathematics writer who made an original contribution to the fields of C*-algebra , symmetric topology and pure mathematics .
Islwyn Morris ( 26 August 1920 -- 26 April 2011 ) was a Welsh - speaking actor and director , best known for his roles in Welsh - language television , such as those of David Tushingham in `` Pobol y Cwm '' and Idris Vaughan in `` Glas y Dorlan '' .
Sara Kristoffersson was born in Stockholm 1972 and is a Swedish writer and professor of design history and theory at Konstfack University College of Arts , Crafts and Design in Stockholm .

Dinç Bilgin ( born 1940 ) is a Turkish businessman who built up a media empire which was seized by the Turkish government in 2002 over alleged financial irregularities .

Robert Youds ( born 1954 in Burnaby , British Columbia ) is a Canadian artist based in Victoria , British Columbia .

Claus E. Heinrich ( 21 June 1955 ) is a German manager , entrepreneur , who is an honorary professor for Operations Research at both the Technical University of Berlin and the University of Mannheim .
Johann Ernst Hanxleden ( 1681 - 1732 ) , famously known as Arnos Paathiri was a German Jesuit priest , missionary in India and a Malayalam / Sanskrit poet , grammarian , lexicographer , and philologist .
Walter Polovchak ( born 3 October 1967 ) is a Ukrainian - American who , as a child , became the center of the legal case Polovchak v. Meese after refusing to leave the United States and return to Ukraine in the Soviet Union with his parents when he was 12 .
Sir Andrew Henderson Leith Fraser , KCSI ( 14 November 1848 -- 26 February 1919 ) was an Indian Civil Servant and the Lieutenant Governor of Bengal between 1903 and 1908 .

Yekta Güngör Özden ( born 1932 ) is a Turkish judge , and former president of the Constitutional Court of Turkey .

Jenkin Jones ( born 1623 ) was a Welsh captain in the army of the Parliamentarians during the English Civil War , and a Puritan cleric and preacher .

Paul Dakeyne ( born 30 January 1963 ) , known by his stage name Tinman , is a British house music producer / remixer .
Deborah Laake ( 1953 -- February 6 , 2000 ) was a columnist at the Dallas Morning News in the 1980s and later a staff writer , columnist , editor , and executive at the Phoenix New Times .
St. Vitalis of Assisi , O.S.B. ( Italian : San Vitale de Assisi ) ( 1295 -- May 31 , 1370 ) , was an Italian hermit and monk .
Moritz Heuzenroeder ( 15 July 1849 -- 10 November 1897 ) was a pianist , composer and teacher of music born in Germany who had a substantial career in South Australia .

Richard Reid Rogers ( 1868 - -November 10 , 1949 ) was a prominent United States lawyer , specializing in transit law .

Tom O'Folliard ( c. 1858 -- December 19 , 1880 ) was the best friend of outlaw William Bonney , a.k.a . Billy the Kid .
Rizwanur Rahman ( 1977 -- 21 September 2007 ) was a 30-year - old computer graphics trainer who committed suicide after marrying Priyanka Todi , daughter of industrialist Ashok Todi .

John Lauritsen ( b. 1939 ) is a retired market research analyst , author , activist , and the founder of Pagan Press .
Johann Christian Wiegleb ( December 21 , 1732 -- January 16 , 1800 ) was a notable German druggist and early innovator of chemistry as a science .
Tridu Songtsen ( Tibetan : ཁྲི་འདུས་སྲོང་བཙན་ , Wylie : Khri ' dus - srong btsan ) , Tridu Songtsän or Dusong Mangban , ( 670 - -704 ; r. 676 - -704 CE ) was an emperor of the Tibetan Empire from 676 to 704 .

Los Pagares de Mendieta is a b&w 1939 Argentine comedy film directed by Leopoldo Torres Ríos .

The Bright Day ( Persian : روز روشن‎‎ ) is a 2013 social drama Iranian film , directed by Hossein Shahabi ( Persian : حسین شهابی ) It is his debut feature film which was very well received by Iranian film critics and audiences of the 31st Fajr Film Festival of Tehran in February 2013 .
Tarnished is a 1950 American action film directed by Harry Keller and written by John K. Butler .
The Great Waldo Pepper is a 1975 drama film directed , produced , and co - written by George Roy Hill .
Sunday Calm is a 1923 short silent comedy film directed by Robert F. McGowan .
Edge of Fury is a 1958 American drama film directed by Robert J. Gurney Jr. and Irving Lerner and written by Robert J. Gurney Jr ..
The Great Dome Robbery is a 2002 crime drama film directed by Gabriel Range , based on the actual Millennium Dome raid of 2000 .
Un uomo ritorna ( also known as Revenge ) is a 1946 Italian drama film directed by Max Neufeld .

Boy and Bicycle is the first film made by Ridley Scott .

Just Another Missing Kid is a 1981 documentary film about the search for a missing teenager and directed by John Zaritsky .
Early Abstractions is a collection of seven short animated films created by Harry Everett Smith between 1939 and 1956 .
The Road Movie trilogy is a series of three road movies directed by German film director Wim Wenders in the mid-1970s .
Chaduvukunna Ammayilu ( Telugu : చదువుకున్న అమ్మాయిలు ) is a 1963 Telugu film produced by Dukkipati Madhusudhana Rao from Annapurna Pictures and directed by Adurthi Subba Rao .

The Preview Murder Mystery is a 1936 American mystery - comedy , directed by Robert Florey and shot in the Paramount studio .

The Roots of Heaven is a 1958 American adventure film in CinemaScope and DeLuxe Color made by 20th Century Fox , directed by John Huston and produced by Darryl F. Zanuck .

Savoy Pictures Entertainment , Inc. was an American independent motion picture company in operation from 1992 to 1997 .

Biała Podlaska Voivodeship ( Polish : województwo bialskopodlaskie ) was a unit of administrative division and local government in Poland in the years 1975 - -1998 , superseded by Lublin Voivodeship .
The County of Sicily was a Norman state comprising the islands of Sicily and Malta from 1071 until 1130 .
The White Motor Company was an American automobile , truck and bus manufacturer from 1900 until 1980 .
After the Treaty of Versailles of 1919 , Germany lost all its colonial possessions , including German New Guinea .
The Province of Nassau ( German : Provinz Nassau ) was a province of Prussia from 1944 to 1945 .

The Kingdom of Bavaria ( German : Königreich Bayern ) was a German state that succeeded the former Electorate of Bavaria in 1805 and continued to exist until 1918 .

SINTEF ( Norwegian : Stiftelsen for industriell og teknisk forskning ) , headquartered in Trondheim , Norway , is the largest independent research organisation in Scandinavia .
The Century Foundation is a progressive think tank headquartered in New York City with an office in Washington , D.C. It was founded as a nonprofit public policy research institution on the belief that the prosperity and security of the United States depends on a mix of effective government , open democracy , and free markets .
Semitan is the company responsible for the comprehensive public transport network of Nantes Métropole , the urban community of the French city of Nantes .
Metaversum GmbH is the Berlin - based startup company behind the 3D virtual world Twinity .

Kaplan International Colleges ( KIC ) is a division of the education company Kaplan Inc. , headquartered in London and founded in 1967 .

Cara Fi ( Love Me ) is a Welsh romantic comedy - drama series that first broadcast in November 2014 on S4C , and was later made available on the BBC iPlayer .
What 's the Story is an American television game show broadcast on the DuMont Television Network from July 25 , 1951 to September 23 , 1955 and aired in eleven different timeslots .
R. K. Laxman Ki Duniya was an Indian comedy TV show on SAB TV .
The Amazing Chan and the Chan Clan ( sometimes abbreviated as The Amazing Chan Clan ) is a 30-minute Saturday morning animated series produced by Hanna - Barbera Productions , animated by Eric Porter Studios in Australia and broadcast on CBS from September 9 , 1972 to December 30 , 1972 .
Wire in the Blood is a British crime drama television series , created and produced by Coastal Productions for the ITV network that ran from 2002 to 2008 .
Jersey No . 10 is an Indian television series that premiered on November 5 , 2007 on SAB TV .
The Last Word with Lawrence O'Donnell is an hour - long weeknight news and political commentary program on MSNBC .
Jenna 's American Sex Star is an adult pay - per - view reality television series hosted by Jenna Jameson on Playboy TV that ran from 2005 until 2006 .
Fox & Friends First is a morning television news program on Fox News Channel .
Saturday Primetime , officially Saturday Primetime presented by DirecTV , is an American television program that appears on ESPN during the college basketball regular season .
Texas Car Wars was an American reality documentary television series on the Discovery Channel .
Ghost Hunters is an American paranormal reality television series that premiered on October 6 , 2004 , on Syfy ( previously the Sci Fi Channel ) .
¡ Mucha Lucha ! ( later known as ¡ Mucha Lucha ! : Gigante ) is an American - Mexican - Canadian animated television series that premiered on Kids ' WB on August 17 , 2002 .

Scotsport was a Scottish sports television programme , broadcast on STV in northern and central Scotland , as well as on ITV Border in southern Scotland .

Palibhasa Lalake ( Just Because ( You 're ) A Man ) is a Philippine TV sitcom series on ABS - CBN which ran from 1987 to 1998 and directed by Johnny Manahan .

Today Acanthopholis is considered a member of the Nodosauridae within the Ankylosauria .
The American cockroach ( Periplaneta americana ) , also colloquially known as the waterbug , but not a true waterbug since it is not aquatic , or misidentified as the palmetto bug ( see Florida woods cockroach for the differences ) , is the largest species of common cockroach , and often considered a pest .
Laevinesta atlantica is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Caspian tyulka , Clupeonella caspia , is a species of fish in the Clupeidae family .
Hippomane is a genus of plants in the Euphorbiaceae described by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Microscopically , Lactarius species have elliptical , rarely globoid spores with amyloid ornamentation in the form of more or less prominent warts or spines , connected by ridges , like other members of the Russulaceae family .
The Rodrigues parrot ( Necropsittacus rodricanus ) is an extinct parrot in the family Psittaculidae .
Underwood 's water mouse ( Rheomys underwoodi ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
The Centralian tree frog ( Litoria gilleni ) is a large species of tree frog native to a small area in central Australia .
Lyciasalamandra is a genus of salamander in the Salamandridae family , native to Turkey and Greece .

The 2001 Jordan League was the 51st season of Jordan Premier League , the top - flight league for Jordanian association football clubs .
The WXW Women 's Championship is the top female professional wrestling title in the World Xtreme Wrestling promotion .
Martine Le Moignan , MBE ( born 28 October 1962 , Guernsey , Channel Islands ) is a former professional squash player , who was one of the game 's leading players in the 1980s and early-1990s .
Mubarak International Stadium ( Arabic : ستاد مبارك الدولي‎ ) is an all - seated association football stadium in Suez , Egypt .
The World Amateur Golf Ranking for men was introduced by the R&A , the governing body of amateur golf outside the United States and Mexico , on 23 January 2007 .
Johanna Ahlm ( born 3 October 1987 ) is a Swedish handball player who plays for FCM Håndbold and the Sweden women 's national handball team .
The 1997 U.S. Women 's Hard Court Championships was a women 's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts at the Stone Mountain Tennis Center in Atlanta , Georgia in the United States that was part of Tier II of the 1997 WTA Tour .
The 2012 Japan Super Series was the ninth super series tournament of the 2012 BWF Super Series in badminton .
The 2013 FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship Division B was the ninth edition of the Division B of the FIBA Europe Under-20 Championship , the second tier of basketball European U-20 championships .
Fredensborg Boldklub og Idrætsforening ( Danish : Fredensborg Ball and Sports Club ) , known as Fredensborg BI , is a Danish association football club located in the municipality of Fredensborg , which plays in the Denmark Series .
Amber Jacobs ( born June 29 , 1982 ) is the assistant athletic director for Summit University and is also their head women 's basketball coach .
Uzi Geller ( Hebrew : עוזי גלר‎ ; born 27 January 1931 , in kibbutz Givat Chaim ) is an Israeli chess master .
The Croatian Chess Federation ( Croatian : Hrvatski šahovski savez , HŠS ) is a chess governing body in Croatia .
Carlos Jiménez Sánchez ( born February 10 , 1976 ) is a Spanish former professional basketball player and current assistant coach of the Unicaja .
Welvis Dias Marcelino , better known as Vivinho ( March 10 , 1961 -- September 13 , 2015 ) , was an association football striker , who played in several Brazilian Série A clubs .
Georgios Amerikanos ( alternate spelling : Giorgos ) ( Greek : Γιώργος Αμερικάνος ; December 21 , 1942 -- October 7 , 2013 ) was a Greek professional basketball player and basketball coach .
Saki Minemura ( 峯村沙紀 Minemura Saki , born April 18 , 1990 ) is a Japanese volleyball player who plays for Toray Arrows .
National League 1 , ( which was known before September 2009 as National Division Two ) , is the third level of domestic rugby union competition in England .
Ronn Tomassoni is a retired American ice hockey player and coach .
The 2011 Mexican Figure Skating Championships were the Mexican Figure Skating Championships of the 2010 - -11 figure skating season .
The Kehoe Cup ( Irish : Corn Mhic Eochaidh ) is an annual hurling competition organised by the Leinster Council of the Gaelic Athletic Association ( GAA ) since 1977 for second- and third - tier inter - county teams in the province of Leinster in Ireland .
The Macon Trax were a minor - league professional ice hockey team based in Macon , Georgia .
Teresa Edwards ( born July 19 , 1964 ) is an American former women 's basketball player .
Qiu Li ( Chinese : 邱礼 , born June 6 , 1981 in Shenyang , Liaoning , China ) is a naturalised Chinese - Singaporean professional association football player .
The 2010 European Trophy was a European ice hockey tournament , played between 11 August and 5 September 2010 .
Derek Edwardson ( born August 26 , 1981 ) is an American born Italian professional ice hockey player who is currently an Unrestricted Free Agent .
The 2006 Orange Prokom Open was the ninth edition of this men 's tennis tournament and was played on outdoor clay courts .
The Royal Belgian Hockey Association ( Dutch : Koninklijke Belgische Hockey Bond ; French : Association Royale Belge de Hockey ) is the governing body for the game of ( field ) hockey in Belgium .
Zaheer Khan ( born 7 October 1978 ) is a former Indian cricketer who was a member of the Indian national cricket team from 2000 till 2014 .
The Hershey Bears are an American professional ice hockey team based in Hershey , Pennsylvania .
Georgi Joseph ( born November 23 , 1982 ) is a French professional basketball player who plays for French Pro A league club ASVEL .
Thomas Briels ( 23 August 1987 , Wilrijk ) is a Belgian international field hockey player .
The British Flyweight Championship is a British flyweight professional wrestling championship currently defended in XWA .
The 2011 Rally Australia was the 21st Rally Australia and the tenth round of the 2011 World Rally Championship season .
Prime Doleshwar Sporting Club is a team that plays List A cricket in the Dhaka Premier League .
The 1996 Danamon Open was a women 's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts at the Gelora Senayan Stadium in Jakarta in Indonesia and was part of Tier III of the 1996 WTA Tour .
Silkeborg - Hallerne is a complex of indoor sports arenas in Silkeborg , Denmark used for several sports , but primarily handball .
On October 3 , 1951 , after watching the New York Giants defeat the Brooklyn Dodgers to win the National League Pennant on a tiny little black and white TV , Ed Lucas , who was just twelve years old , went out to play baseball with his friends .
Mario Ledesma Arocena ( born 17 May 1973 in Buenos Aires ) is an Argentine rugby union football coach and a former professional player .
The Royal Moroccan Athletics Federation ( Fédération Royale Marocaine d’Athlétisme , FRMA ) is Morocco 's governing body for the sport of athletics .
AMSL Fréjus Volleyball ( Association municipale des sports et loisirs de Fréjus volley - ball ) is a French volleyball club , section of the AMSL Fréjus multi - sports club , which now plays in the fourth division , but in its history has several national titles .
Mohammad Fanaei ( born 23 December 1951 in Tehran , Iran ) is a former Iranian association football ( soccer ) referee .
Nonito Donaire vs. Guillermo Rigondeaux was a professional boxing match fought in the super bantamweight division .
The 1998 Sydney International was a tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts at the NSW Tennis Centre in Sydney in Australia that was part of the International Series of the 1998 ATP Tour and of Tier II of the 1998 WTA Tour .
FSV Braunfels is a German association football club established in 1918 in Braunfels , Hesse .
The 2011 ITU Sprint Distance Triathlon World Championships was a triathlon race organised by the International Triathlon Union ( ITU ) held in Lausanne , Switzerland on August 20 .
The Chess'n Math Association ( or Chess and Math Association ) is a non - profit organization dedicated to bringing chess into Canadian schools .
SK Horácká Slavia Třebíč is an ice hockey team in Třebíč , Czech Republic .
William Hopoate also known as Viliami in Tonga ( born 9 May 1992 ) is an Australian professional rugby league footballer who currently plays for the Canterbury - Bankstown Bulldogs in the National Rugby League .
The Eurobowl is both the final game and the trophy of the BIG6 European Football League ( BIG6 ) , a European American football contest .
Sensible Soccer , often affectionately known as Sensi , is an association football video game series which was highly popular in the early 1990s and which still retains a cult following .

Chantal de Bruijn ( born February 13 , 1976 in Schoonhoven ) is a Dutch field hockey defender who has played for Dutch clubs Shinty , SV Kampong and Amsterdam .
The 1997 Danamon Open was a women 's tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts at the Gelora Senayan Stadium in Jakarta in Indonesia and was part of Tier IV of the 1997 WTA Tour .
Mitch Unrein ( born March 25 , 1987 ) is an American football defensive end and Goaline Fullback for the Chicago Bears of the National Football League ( NFL ) .
The Liga Portuguesa de Basquetebol ( English : Portuguese Basketball League ) is the top men 's basketball league in Portugal .
Nolan Richardson , Jr. ( born December 27 , 1941 ) is an American basketball head coach best known for his tenure at the University of Arkansas , where he won the 1994 NCAA Men 's Division I Basketball Tournament .
The 1988 WTA German Open was a women 's tennis tournament played on outdoor clay courts at the Rot - Weiss Tennis Club in West Berlin and was part of Tier I of the 1988 WTA Tour .
Jordy Hultberg , a former LSU basketball player ( 1976 - -80 ) and assistant basketball coach under Dale Brown ( 1980 - -83 ) , is the sideline reporter for the LSU Sports Radio Network as well as the New Orleans Hornets on Cox Sports Television .
Orla Hermann Krause ( 3 November 1867 -- 28 September 1935 ) was a Danish chess master and analyst .

Stephen Oziegebe Ojomoh , known as Steve Ojomoh ( born Benin City , 25 May 1970 ) , is a Nigerian - born English former rugby union footballer and a current coach .

Mirko Novosel ( born June 30 , 1938 in Zagreb , Kingdom of Yugoslavia ) is a retired Croatian basketball player , referee and coach .

The Central Coast Centurions were an Australian rugby league football club ( previously known as the Rip or Storm ) based in the Central Coast region in New South Wales .

The Beauce Jaros were a minor professional ice hockey team from Saint - Georges , Quebec , located in the `` Beauce '' region of the province .
The 1987 PBA All - Filipino Conference Finals was the best - of-5 basketball championship series of the 1987 PBA All - Filipino Conference , and the conclusion of the conference playoffs .
The 1989 Singapore Open ( known as Epson Singapore Super Tennis for sponsorship reasons ) was a tennis tournament played on outdoor hard courts at the National Stadium in Singapore and was part of the 1989 Nabisco Grand Prix .
Jørgen Møller ( sometimes Jorgen Moeller or Jörgen Möller ) ( 4 November 1873 -- 20 November 1944 ) was a Danish chess master .
