La Plata Rugby Club is a rugby union club from the city of La Plata in the province of Buenos Aires , Argentina .
The 2012 Women 's Baseball World Cup was an international baseball competition being held in Edmonton , Alberta , Canada from August 10 to August 19 , 2012 .
The 1969 NBA All - Star Game was an exhibition basketball game which was played on January 14 , 1969 , at the Baltimore Civic Center in Baltimore , Maryland .
The Oval , currently known for sponsorship reasons as the Kia Oval , is an international cricket ground at Kennington , in the London Borough of Lambeth , South London .
Treaty City Titans are an Irish semi - professional rugby league team based in Limerick , Ireland .
Athinaikos H.C. is a Greek handball club based in Vyronas , Athens .
Nicole Bradtke ( née Provis ) ( born 22 September 1969 ) is a retired professional tennis player from Australia .
Sophia of Minsk ( or Sophia of Polotsk ) ( c. 1140 -- 5 May 1198 ) was a Danish medieval queen consort as the spouse of King Valdemar I of Denmark , and later a landgravine of Thuringia .
Eärendil later became the leader of the people who lived there , and married Elwing , daughter of Dior the son of Beren and Lúthien .
April Cantelo married the conductor Colin Davis in 1949 .
Papia of Envermeu , also called Poppa of Envermeu , was the second consort of Richard II , Duke of Normandy .
Stella Richman married three times ; her first husband was the actor Alec Clunes .
Hedvig Mörner af Morlanda ( 1672 - -1753 ) , was a Swedish courtier and countess , married to riksråd count Claes Ekeblad the Elder .
Joan Mondale ( née Adams ; August 8 , 1930 -- February 3 , 2014 ) was Second Lady of the United States from 1977 until 1981 as the wife of Walter Mondale , the 42nd Vice President of the United States .
Alvin Rakoff married his frequent leading lady , actress Jacqueline Hill in 1958 .
Jackie Autry , ( born Jacqueline Evelyn Ellam October 2 , 1941 in Newark , New Jersey , US ) is the former owner of the Los Angeles Angels of Anaheim and widow of singer , actor and businessman Gene Autry .
Lien Fang Yu ( traditional Chinese : 連方瑀 ; simplified Chinese : 连方瑀 ; pinyin : Lián Fāng Yǔ ) born April 14 , 1943 in Chongqing as Fang Yu ( Chinese : 方瑀 ; pinyin : Fāng Yǔ ) , is the wife of Lien Chan , the Chairman of Taiwan 's Kuomintang party from 2000 to 2005 .
Hugh Talbot ( c. 1845 -- 31 October 1899 ) was an Irish tenor and actor best known for creating , to universally bad reviews , the role of Frederic in the Gilbert and Sullivan hit The Pirates of Penzance in the New York production .
Gail Varina Gilmore ( born September 21 , 1950 in Washington , D.C. ) is an African - American Gospel , jazz and ( mezzo - soprano ) opera singer .
Marina Domashenko ( Russian : Марина Домашенко ) is a Russian operatic mezzo - soprano .
Patricia Leonard ( 9 March 1936 -- 28 January 2010 ) was an English opera singer , best known for her performances in mezzo - soprano and contralto roles of the Savoy Operas with the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company .
Alois Pernerstorfer ( 3 June 1912 , Vienna -- 12 May 1978 , Vienna ) was an Austrian bass - baritone He began his training in 1933 at the Wiener Musikhochschule with Theo Lierhammer and Josef Krips and made his opera debut in 1936 in Graz singing the role of Biterolf in Tannhäuser .
María Cristina Kiehr ( born in Tandil , Argentina ) is a soprano vocalist associated with Baroque music .
Rosa Raisa ( 30 May 1893 -- 28 September 1963 ) was a Polish - born and Italian - trained Russian - Jewish dramatic operatic soprano who became a naturalized American .
Renata Scotto ( born 24 February 1934 ) is an Italian soprano and opera director .
Marie Cabel ( 31 January 1827 -- 23 May 1885 ) was a Belgian coloratura soprano .
Elsa Stralia ( 1 March 1881 -- 31 August 1945 ) was an Australian soprano with an international reputation in Europe and America .
Teresa De Giuli Borsi , born Maria Teresa Pippeo , ( 26 October 1817 -- 18 November 1877 ) was an Italian opera singer who excelled in the dramatic soprano repertoire of the mid-19th century .
Shirley Love ( born January 6 , 1940 ) is an American operatic mezzo - soprano .
Ottilie Metzger - Lattermann also formerly Ottilie Metzger - Froitzheim ( 15 July 1878 -- February 1943 ) was a German contralto who was a famous performer of works by Wagner during the 1910s , and who after her retirement was murdered in Auschwitz .
Ilona Jokinen ( b. 1981 Lahti , Finland ) is a Finnish soprano opera singer .
Angela Meade ( born 1977 ) is an award winning American operatic soprano who is particularly associated with the Metropolitan Opera in New York City .
Alice Nielsen ( June 7 , 1872 -- March 8 , 1943 ) was a Broadway performer and operatic soprano who had her own opera company and starred in several Victor Herbert operettas .
Lucrezia Bori ( 24 December 1887 -- 14 May 1960 ) was a Spanish operatic singer , a lyric soprano and a tireless and effective fundraiser for the Metropolitan Opera .
Richard Kubla ( 11 February 1890 -- 9 July 1964 ) was a Czech tenor who had an active international career in operas , concerts , and recitals from 1910 - 1945 .
Giannina Russ ( 27 March 1873 , Lodi -- 28 February 1951 , Milan ) was an Italian operatic soprano , particularly associated with the Italian repertory .
Amarilli Nizza ( born January 4 , 1971 in Milan ) is an Italian operatic soprano .
Giulio Gari ( September 9 , 1909 - April 15 , 1994 ) was a versatile and internationally known tenor who performed on both the opera and concert stages .
Walther Ludwig ( 17 March 1902 , Bad Oeynhausen -- 15 May 1981 , Lahr ) was a German operatic lyric tenor , particularly associated with Mozart roles and Schubert lieder .
Robin Miriam Carlsson ( born 12 June 1979 ) , known as Robyn , is a Swedish soprano vocalist .
Stella Roman ( 23 August 1904 - 12 February 1992 ) was a Romanian operatic soprano whose career brought her leading roles in Italy and the United States .
Marcus Ullmann ( born 1967 in Dresden ) is a German classical tenor .
Marquita Lister ( born 24 April 1961 ) is an American operatic soprano .
Björk has a soprano vocal range , which has been described as both `` elastic '' and `` somersaulting '' in quality as well as having been praised for her scatting ability , unique vocal stylings and delivery .
Teodor Ilincăi ( born in Mălini , Suceava County ) is a Romanian opera tenor .
Karin Branzell ( 24 September 1891 -- 15 December 1974 ) was a Swedish operatic contralto ( sometimes described as a mezzo - soprano ) , who had a prominent career at the Metropolitan Opera , New York , and in Europe .
Nico Castel ( August 1 , 1931 -- May 31 , 2015 ) , born Naftali Chaim Castel Kalinhoff , was a comprimario tenor and well - known language and diction coach , as well as a prolific translator of libretti and writer of books on singing diction .
Aluna Sagita Gutawa ( born 11 August 1993 in Jakarta ) , better known as Gita Gutawa , is an Indonesian soprano , actress , and songwriter .
Marilyn Cotlow ( born January 10 , 1924 ) is an American lyric coloratura soprano best remembered for originating the role of Lucy in Gian Carlo Menotti 's The Telephone .
Olaf Bär ( born December 19 , 1957 in Dresden ) is a German operatic baritone .
Ann Drummond - Grant ( 1905 -- 11 September 1959 ) was a British singer and actress , best known for her performances in contralto roles of the Gilbert and Sullivan operas with the D'Oyly Carte Opera Company .
Anna Prohaska ( Neu - Ulm , 1983 ) is an Austrian coloratura soprano .
Suzanna Guzmán ( born in East Los Angeles , California ) is an American mezzo - soprano and television host .
Rachele Gilmore is an American coloratura soprano born in Atlanta .
Marcel Journet ( July 25 , 1868 -- September 7 , 1933 ) , was a French , bass , operatic singer .
Célestine Galli - Marié ( November 1840 -- 22 September 1905 ) was a French mezzo - soprano who is most famous for creating the title role in the opera Carmen .
Carlton Gauld ( before 1931 -- after 1960 ) was an American operatic bass who had a prolific career during the 1930s through the 1960s .
Josef Traxel ( 29 September 1916 in Mainz -- 8 October 1975 in Stuttgart ) was a German operatic tenor , particularly associated with Mozart roles and the German repertory .
Lucia Valentini Terrani ( 29 August 1946 in Padua -- 11 June 1998 in Seattle ) was an Italian coloratura mezzo - soprano , particularly associated with Rossini roles .
Gloria Banditelli ( Assisi , 16 February 1954 ) is an Italian mezzo - soprano .
Jean Giraudeau ( 1 July 1916 in Toulon -- 7 February 1995 ) , was a French tenor , and later theatre director , particularly associated with the Opéra - Comique in Paris , and described in Grove as having a `` lyrical voice '' as well as being `` a superb character actor '' .
Paul Ukena ( August 19 , 1921 , Lakota , Iowa - March 10 , 1991 , Mount Vernon , New York ) was an American operatic baritone who had an active career during the 1950s through the 1970s .
Licia Albanese ( July 22 , 1909 -- August 15 , 2014 ) was an Italian - born American operatic soprano .
Gianna D'Angelo ( 18 November 1929 - 27 December 2013 ) was an American coloratura soprano , primarily active in the 1950s and 1960s .
Juliette Pochin is a Welsh classically trained mezzo - soprano singer , composer / arranger , and record producer .
María Georgina Quitral Espinoza , commonly known as Rayén Quitral ( 7 November 1916 -- 20 October 1979 ) , was a Chilean soprano of Mapuche - Picunche origin .
Luise Willer ( 1888 - -1970 ) was a German operatic contralto .
